value.literal: Convert a number, represented as a sequence of digits in one base, to any other base.
Will convert anything from base 2 to base 10 or vice versa.
Input a number and its inbase and outbase.
The inbase represents the starting base and the outbase represents the base you want to convert to.
For example, when converting 42 base 10 to base 2, the number you want to convert is 42, the inbase is 10 and the outbase is base 2.
